comments:
Strengths: 
- Really great reading material;
- Professor Ehrgood is an amazing teacher;
- Themes for the essays were often challenging, but diverse enough to force us to expand our horizons as writers;
- Seminar discussions were very engaging;
- Workshops were super helpful and fun.

How this course could be improved:
- At some points, I felt like I didn't have as much time as I would have liked to have had to work on some revisions of essays earlier on in the term, but as we reached Essays 4 and 5, I felt like I could definitely have been done with them in less time. Maybe in the future some of this extra time that was given for us to work on the last two essays could be reallocated to the first couple of essays.
